FBIS3-53708 "drnes012_p_94004" FBIS-NES-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Hekmatyar Rejects Proposal on Mediation Council LD1801192094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1830 GMT 18 Jan 94 LD1801192094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Language: Persian Article Type:BFN [Text] Hekmatyar's Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic Party of Afghanistan] has rejected a plan proposed by Ahmad Shah Mas'ud, that suggested a 15-member council should mediate between the warring factions in Afghanistan. According to an IRNA report, the Hezb-e Eslami spokesman said: Hekmatyar's Hezb-e Eslami considers this proposal as an effort to create a rift between Afghanistan's Jihadi groups. Furthermore, the Hezb-e Wahdat-e Eslami-e [Islamic Unity Party of Afghanistan] spokesman in Peshawar told IRNA: The resolution of the Afghan problem can only be accomplished by agreement among the four major parties in that country; that is Hezb-e Eslami, Hezb-e Wahdat, Jonbesh-e Shomal [the Northern Movement] and Rabbani's Jami'at-e Eslami [Islamic Society of Afghanistan].
